{"id":"428835640537739_472548712833098","type":"photo","created_time":"2013-05-24T20:04:15+0000","message":"The 'qoumis' were under scrutiny, if not from the country's own agencies, but curiously from external agencies. \r\n\r\nA recent WikiLeaks release reveals that the US embassy in Bangladesh had been closely watching and monitoring the activities of Qoumi madrasahs during 2008-09. \r\n\r\nIn a cable sent to Washington from the then US ambassador in 2009, Qoumi madrasahs in the Rajshahi region were mentioned as strongholds of militants. \r\n\r\nA more convincing statement mentioned in the cable was that the 'qoumis' were filling in the void that existed in the country's educational arena with free food and lodging to the vast number of impoverished children whose parents were in no position to feed them, not to speak of giving them education. \r\n\r\nThe cable reportedly further states that the suspicious funding source of the 'qoumis', provocative learning materials and their close ties with protectionist elements are clear enough proofs of the government's failure to play any worthwhile role in the field. \r\n\r\nhttp:\/\/www.thefinancialexpress-bd.com\/index.php?ref=MjBfMDVfMjVfMTNfMV82XzE3MDQ2Ng==","picture":"https:\/\/fbcdn-photos-g-a.akamaihd.net\/hphotos-ak-ash3\/581897_472548689499767_858422597_s.png"}